<subSubSection id="C332E78EFF90015D031F83EBFBF3FA7D" pageId="1" pageNumber="621" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B97B405FF90015D031F83EBFBF3FA7D" blockId="1.[835,1475,1220,1468]" pageId="1" pageNumber="621">
<emphasis id="B95C6817FF90015D031F83EBFC1FFB1D" bold="true" box="[835,946,1220,1244]" pageId="1" pageNumber="621">Remarks.</emphasis>
The present material agrees well with the 
<typeStatus id="54930AA7FF90015D05C883EAFA6FFB1C" box="[1428,1474,1221,1245]" pageId="1" pageNumber="621">type</typeStatus>
description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C28CF86FF90015D03BF83CAFBD6FB3D" authorityName="Komai &amp; Rahayu" authorityYear="2004" box="[995,1147,1252,1276]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Pagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="621" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fungiformis">
<emphasis id="B95C6817FF90015D03BF83CAFBD6FB3D" box="[995,1147,1252,1276]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="621">P. fungiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB9C9F4FF90015D04F583CBFA12FB3D" author="Komai T &amp; Rahayu DL" box="[1193,1471,1252,1276]" pageId="1" pageNumber="621" pagination="183 - 200" refId="ref17841" refString="Komai T &amp; Rahayu DL (2004) Redescription of Pagurus moluccensis Haig &amp; Ball, 1988, and description of a new species of Pagurus from Indonesia (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura: Paguridae). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 52: 183 - 200." type="journal article" year="2004">Komai &amp; Rahayu (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. As has been discussed by the original authors, this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C28CF86FF90015D03EC820AFBE1FAFD" authorityName="Haig &amp; Ball" authorityYear="1988" box="[944,1100,1316,1340]" class="Malacostraca" family="Paguridae" genus="Pagurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="621" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moluccensis">
<emphasis id="B95C6817FF90015D03EC820AFBE1FAFD" box="[944,1100,1316,1340]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="621">P. moluccensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the general morphology and the coloration in life (cf. 
<figureCitation id="1313A880FF90015D0441826BFB21FA9D" box="[1053,1164,1348,1372]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[113,148,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[199,1368,622,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-372@2.[199,1368,622,1952]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. A, Pagurus fungiformis Komai &amp; Rahayu, 2004, male (sl 2.7 mm), PANGLAO 2004, stn M51, Mayacabac, Panglao Island, ZRC 2013.0645; B, Pagurus kulkarnii Sankolli, 1962, male (sl mm), PANGLAO 2004, stn R66, Sungcolan inlet, Panglao Island, ZRC 2014.0300; C, Pagurus moluccensis Haig &amp; Ball, 1988, male (sl 3.2 mm), PANGLAO 2004, stn M2, west end of Alona Beach, Panglao Island, ZRC 2013.0644; D, Pagurus pergranulatus (Henderson, 1896), PANGLAO 2004, stn R16, Black Forest, Balicasag Island, ovigerous female (sl 6.0 mm), ZRC 2014.0301." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5355010" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5355010/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="621">Fig. 1A, C</figureCitation>
), but it is readily recognisable by the unique, characteristic armature of the palms of both chelae, consisting of closely set, low, rounded tubercles with multi-denticulate margins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
